summary: I can't help but associating this song with villaneve. In Paris after everything is said and done. Having cute little dates in...
caption: I can’t help but associating this song with villaneve. In Paris after everything is said and done. Having cute little dates in every cafe that catch their eyes. Sometimes just because the smell of their freshly baked pastries are too strong for either of them to ignore. Or in the morning, when the rays of the sun slip through the curtains and slowly waking them up from their peaceful slumber. Or those dusks when Eve watches Villanelle skips through the street on her yet another elaborate and quirky dresses. A couple steps behind her, slightly smiling because they are in Paris and she is deeply in love.

summary: I’ve been thinking about this a lot since reading Sharp Objects and watching Killing Eve, but I think it’s interesting the ways...
body: I’ve been thinking about this a lot since reading Sharp Objects and watching Killing Eve, but I think it’s interesting the ways that violent/hurtful women and women with a history of trauma and/or serious self-image issues end up interacting in intense (perhaps even dangerous) ways. I think one of the reasons this happens in interesting ways and with such frequency is because there exists a kind of taboo on female darkness; women are not permitted to express negative emotions or be negative presences, so we often conceal these feelings/impulses and only reveal them in private and with a limited number of people. Because of this I think that women who hate themselves and hurt inwardly are collapsed with women who hate and hurt others, and when an instance of one category finds an instance of the other there’s a sort of relief and recognition that quickly mutates into a relationship with an extreme power imbalance. This is further exacerbated by the tendency of the self-hurting individual to exert an enormous amount of effort to understand and comfort the other-hurting individual in a fairly classic case of codependency.
